# Checking Multiple Conditions 

In our previous control flow we only used `if` and `else`, but that only works
if you have **one** condition you need to check. Since we are dealing with more
than one condition to check (spoiler!), we will need another control flow.

`else if ()` works similar to an `if ()` statement, where you give it a
condition to check. This is how we can chain **multiple** conditions. 

```
if (condition 1) {
  stuff to do 
} else if (condition 2) {
  other stuff to do
} else {
  other other stuff to do
}
```
:::

::: {.callout-note collapse=TRUE}
# Check Your Answer


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
if (income < 11925) {
  tax <- 0.10
  } else if (income <= 48475) {
    tax <- 0.12
  } else if (income <= 103350) {
    tax <- 0.22
  } else if (income <= 197300) {
    tax <- 0.24
  } else if (income <= 250525) {
    tax <- 0.32
  } else if (income < 626350){
    tax <- 0.35
  } else {
    tax <- 0.37
  }
```
:::

